      "title": "Another Sri Lankan man dies while waiting for fuel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Another Sri Lankan family lost their bread-winner who was at a fuel queue.",
        "A 53-year-old father of two died after he was knocked down by a lorry in Darga Town, Aluthgama while waiting for fuel last night.",
        "Report said that he was preparing to leave the filling station and head home when the tragedy struck.",
        "The driver of the Mathugama-bound lorry surrendered to the Police this morning.",
        "NO Petrol Shipment until 22nd July; 100,000 MT LP Gas available for next four months \u2013 Sagala Ratnayake",
        "\u2018One Country, One Law\u2019 Task Force submits report to President"
